header.gameNote: SMU HOLIDAY CLASSIC AT DALLAS TX

article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 98, Paul Quinn 62
article.story: DALLAS (AP) -- Matt Kingsley had 25 points, seven rebounds and four blocks to lead Stephen F. Austin past Paul Quinn 98-62 Saturday. Kingsley made 10 of 13 field goals to offset a rough 5-of-12 outing on free throws for the Lumberjacks (10-1). Josh Alexander was 5-of-11 from 3-point range and finished with 22 points. Jazz Henderson led Paul Quinn (6-7) with 15 points, most of it coming on free throws (9-of-12). Larry Ivey added 12. Alexander had two 3-pointers and a free throw and Alexander scored the other four points during an 11-2 run that put Stephen F. Austin ahead 42-26 with 2:50 remaining in the first half. The Lumberjacks scored the first 11 points of the second half to take a 55-29 lead. Alexander had nine of the points, including a 3-pointer that capped the run with 16:55 left.
